Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop them onto
a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{},
then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl{}, combine the garlic, @panko breadcrumbs{10%g}, @salt{1/4%tsp}
and @water{2%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs.

Add the @British beef mince{240%g} to the breadcrumbs. Season with @pepper{} and
mix together with your hands.

Roll into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per person.

> TIP: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the burgers onto another baking tray.

When the oven is hot, bake on the middle shelf until cooked through,
~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, halve the @glazed burger buns{2}.

When the wedges have a few mins left, pop the buns into the oven to warm through,
~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, pop the buns on your plates.

Spread the @redcurrant jelly{25%g} over the lids and the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}
over the bases. Stack with a burger, then the @crumbled blue cheese{30%g} and
@wild rocket{20%g} before sandwiching shut.

Serve your burgers with the wedges alongside. Enjoy!